Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.25,0:01:32.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Seebühl Village {ゼービュール村}{im taking names from the book because if we hear them say this german way, writing Bohrlaken would be discrepant}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.14,0:01:44.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,Bühlsee Lake {ビュールゼー湖}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.64,0:01:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so peaceful here.{/calm}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.08,0:01:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No better place to spend your holiday than the countryside.{ after all}{unsure what they mean as kagiru is "limit/boundary"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.76,0:01:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's change the point from our usual one today.{unsure, I think they call point the spot where they do fishing}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.51,0:01:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with those children?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.04,0:02:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls from Viennese{hope that the meaning of this wuinne} elementary schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.95,0:02:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They are living in a summer camp.{I hope this is the meaning of "children's house"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.49,0:02:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Summer camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.87,0:02:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls from various school come together \Nto spend their vacation here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.71,0:02:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There, that red-roofed building{ over there} is where they live.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.91,0:02:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, they are making a lot of fuss. \NEnough to make this point unfit for fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.47,0:02:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely. We'd be better off someplace away from them.{/on the opposite side}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.64,0:02:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,For an urbanite, you reasoning is quite sound.{no clue what he means by "for a city dweller, good feeling/sensation"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.82,0:02:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey-hey, I'm not that stupid! {/can't be jesting that much}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.67,0:02:35.72,Sign,,0,0,116,,{\c&HD2E6F0&\bord0\blur1\xshad2}Episode 1 \N{出会い} {\fs55} Meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.11,0:02:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, let's get out of the water \Nand have a little break!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.21,0:02:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.24,0:02:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We were swimming over there just a moment ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.97,0:02:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise Palfy{here, I take names from english version instead because they sound better in english}! Hurry up to the shore!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.26,0:03:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.46,0:03:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.51,0:03:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise... Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.59,0:03:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be fooling around in the lake, \Nhow many times did I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.11,0:03:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't fooling around, Fraulein Ulrica.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.13,0:03:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Merely practicing to better hold my breath underwater.{rather she says "was checking out for how long can my breath last, practicing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.31,0:03:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I'm well aware of your fondness \Nfor challenging others' authority{/pushing your boundaries}.{rather the eexact meaning is inquisitive mind; spirit of inquiry; spirit of enquiry but I'm deviating here to make it sound more consequent}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.87,0:03:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, get on the shore now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.40,0:03:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.75,0:03:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.71,0:03:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't change one bit this year either, \Nthis Seebühl Village.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.67,0:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's so serene.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe even too quiet! \NIt becomes outright eerie when night comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Monica is saying that because she misses her mom from Vienna greatly and spent last evening sobbing in her bed!{I don't know what is has to do with previous line}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.64,0:03:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lies! All lies! Don't believe it, people!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.63,0:03:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Monica is still so dependent.{/spoiled/child who always demands attention}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.47,0:03:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I, in turn, am enjoying a break \Nfrom my annoying mom's attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.78,0:04:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Christine, you're much prettier this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.70,0:04:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so? But it's a pain to weave.{I hope this is what she means by trouble; difficulty - I can't be bothered to do it}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.60,0:04:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do it for you.{I hope she means this and not "I'm doing this for myself"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.99,0:04:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Luise, let's give you a braid, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.17,0:04:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.70,0:04:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not making use of such great hair is a crime!{/it's a waste to have such beautiful hair through such pains}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.26,0:04:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, everyone, you can go swim again.{/enter the water}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.42,0:04:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.54,0:04:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.39,0:04:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure is snappish, our Luise.{/short tempered}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.58,0:04:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She is actually very kind.{im not sure what she means by "but a totally good girl"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.97,0:04:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Having spent my whole life \Nin the same class, I know for sure -
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,she is bristling against others doing her hair, \Nbecause it's not in her habit, that's all.{/she hates it when others are messing/fiddling with ... because she never had anyone doing it for her i'm sure}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.47,0:04:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in her habit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.65,0:04:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She had to grow up without a mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.27,0:04:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet you'd never tell by the looks.{/she looks nothing like that}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.55,0:04:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But her dad is a real big fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.38,0:04:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A famous composer, \Nand a head conductor of the Vienna Philharmonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.85,0:04:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone in our school knows about that.{/very famous in our school}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.35,0:04:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you try to ridicule her dad, \Nshe's not letting it slide!{/those who tease her for her dad are in big trouble}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Might even slap you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.41,0:04:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, hurry up and change. \NIt's almost lunchtime.{I hope it's what she means by saying it's noon}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:04:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure no one's left behind!{minna e? yuugae? ugai? wasurenaide - no clue what's the first word}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.16,0:05:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, a minute of your attention please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.49,0:05:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Muthesius{found in the book} has something to tell to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.30,0:05:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you all to listen to me while you eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.58,0:05:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This afternoon, we expect more of our friends to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.11,0:05:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty new girls from elementary schools of Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.60,0:05:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.74,0:05:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty of them!{/isn't it}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Within this summer camp, \Nyou are all to become their temporary mentors.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.68,0:05:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Please introduce them to our way of life \Nwith all due geniality.{/kindly teach them various things}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.33,0:05:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We want you to start getting along soon, learn about their towns and schools and tell them about yours.{/exchange/tell and listen about each other's ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.95,0:05:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us all enjoy this summer vacation together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.57,0:05:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.40,0:05:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls from Munich. \NI wonder if they are a lot different from us.{/what kind of girls}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.28,0:05:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just be happy \Nif they are not ill-tempered.{/rude/bullies}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.51,0:05:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Have nothing to fear, Stephie.{this one is Stephiee both in german and english versions but without e it sounds closer to japanese} \NIf anyone tries to mess with you, I'll show them their place.{/I won't allow/forgive it}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.38,0:05:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, you think they'll bring along \Nanything interesting to play with?{unsure what to make of 遊び道具 here, maybe sports equipment?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.89,0:05:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, maybe a big new ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.06,0:05:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine one started leaking air recently.{/letting out/deflating}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.17,0:05:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need a ball, \Ncan't you borrow Brigitte's one?{/speaking of balls, did'nt ... have one}{from german ver, didn't check english one}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.25,0:06:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That one is a dead end.{rather, she says "you can't rely on that person"} \NShe shut it in a locker and hid the key.{kagi wo kakechatta seems to mean just "lock with a/turn the key" but this sounds bad with one lock already present in the sentence}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.48,0:06:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's a brand new item!{/I only/barely bought it}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.52,0:06:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't lend it to someone as barbaric \Nas Luise or her friends.{/violent}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.71,0:06:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Miser girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.41,0:06:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope they bring along some new game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.77,0:06:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There {\i1}should{\i0} be at least one!\N Let's make friends with them to start playing it soon! {/someone surely has, let's hurry up to become friends and play together}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the bus! Bus is coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.90,0:06:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is your stop, young Frauleins.{/we've arrived}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.74,0:06:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful! That seems like a lot of heavy luggage on you.{unsure what he means by everyone's luggage is heavy}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.47,0:06:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There, let me help you with this, heigh-ho.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.84,0:07:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and you too, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.24,0:07:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, careful, like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.63,0:07:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, look there! \NThis girl is carrying a ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope someone brings a set for playing bagatelle!{コリントゲーム - Corinth game / Corinthian bagatelle - usually I'd keep "corinth game" but here it's not distinctively wasei and besides, hadly anyone knows about either versions of this game; unsure what's ban}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.94,0:07:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy your holiday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.25,0:07:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.09,0:07:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.02,0:07:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon. \NYou come from Munich, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.05,0:07:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Mind showing us the way to the dorms?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.98,0:07:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.98,0:07:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.77,0:07:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.95,0:07:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the Frauleins got left behind?{/one more}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.09,0:07:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's wrong, little one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.26,0:07:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I stayed behind to see \Nthat nobody forgets anything.{/was checking if ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That is very thoughtful of you. \NNow, your hand... {/climb down}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.09,0:07:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, what did you do to your hair?{very general question, may be anything - why are you here}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually bristling against others doing your hair, \Nsuddenly you are wearing pigtails?{/you're supposed to hate it when other mess with your hair, but what's with those braids?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.04,0:08:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, next time you want them braided, \Nlet me do it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.13,0:08:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!{guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.11,0:08:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.65,0:08:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Truda!{english version has it trudie which i don't mind too} Did girls from Munich arrive already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.12,0:08:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.92,0:08:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? Something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.83,0:08:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just...{/because}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be... What's this? {/really what is this}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.86,0:08:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What... What's going on?{/hot did this happen}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, should apologize first, at least!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Unruly child.{/troublesome}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.92,0:08:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to see you're here.{/thanks for your work} \NAll girls but one checked in...{/however, you're one child short}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.19,0:08:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. This one.{/there's this child}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.28,0:09:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not Luise Palfy, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.37,0:09:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Truda, Luise... Find{/call} Luise, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.30,0:09:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is urgent!{/hurry up}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.22,0:09:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is big, people! \NHear this, hear this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.28,0:09:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't believe what has happened! \NI just saw Luise two!{/an unbelievable major incident occured, louse has become two}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.75,0:09:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.63,0:09:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.17,0:09:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm more or less content \Nwith this proposed meal plan.{/generally, this 献立 is good - schedule of cooking/dishes or smt like that i think}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.11,0:09:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,However, just on this one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.53,0:09:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Muthesius, twenty new girls \Nfrom Munich have all safely arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.46,0:09:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, glad to know. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.59,0:09:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What I meant to say is, on this one day, \Nwe planned an outing for children.{/trip}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.50,0:09:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something else...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.72,0:09:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:09:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A peculiar thing concerning Luise Palfy.{/it's about ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of trick she pulled this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.81,0:10:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not exactly something {\i1}she{\i0} did...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.48,0:10:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enter now, you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.36,0:10:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's this all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.61,0:10:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Had I been wearing spectacles, \NI'd wipe them right about now!{/have my eyes finally gone bad}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.17,0:10:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The one with the pigtails - \Narrived from Munich today, Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.20,0:10:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte Körner, Frau.{taking german variant here because it totally doesn't sound like horn and just writing kerena is a dick move}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Like two beans in a pod, you two. \NAre you relatives, perchance?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.08,0:10:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, one had never met another up until today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.53,0:10:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What a puzzling turn of events...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.51,0:10:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it puzzling?{unsure what exactly she means} \NThat's just the most natural thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.19,0:10:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,One was brought up in Vienna, \Nthe other was brought up in Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.60,0:10:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I find puzzling.{/I didn't mean that}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, let's not make too big a fuss over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.22,0:10:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A striking resemblance.{/really alike}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.56,0:10:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Two girls so alike are bound to make good friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.23,0:10:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.36,0:11:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.70,0:11:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, not like anyone would force you to. \NYou two are free to work this out by yourselves.{/there's no need to rush unnecessarily, I'll leave that to you two - no clue what she means in the last part, lit is "you can both say that"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.63,0:11:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise is at it again...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.14,0:11:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a moment, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me write down your name, before I forgot.{/without delay}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.06,0:11:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"Lotte Körner," isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.08,0:11:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When and where have you been born?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.30,0:11:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Also names of the parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.10,0:11:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My family is just mother and me.{/I don't have anyone but mom}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.96,0:11:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Then, let's start with the date of birth.{no clue what is hikara, most likely "from day" but what does it mean? "we start from the day, then month then year"? kinda dumb}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.73,0:11:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise. Hey, answer, Luise. \NWhat's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.69,0:11:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.28,0:11:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't understand a thing. \NStill... Still, I don't like it one bit already!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.88,0:11:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, this one is Lotte.\NWord is, she came from Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.52,0:12:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A spitting image!{/like two beans in a pod}\NIf you ask me which is which, I'd never tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.87,0:12:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting constantly pointed at for the rest of my vacations, \Nbecause another girl has the same face!{/from now on, my time here is together with a girl that ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.84,0:12:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Takes some nerve to act like that!{atsukamashii is impudent; shameless; brazen; cheeky; presumptuous but i dunno what it means here, either she says "you're being ..." or "this is so ... of her"}{this is the way book has it: " wouldn't  stand  for  it,"  said  Trudie,  a  schoolmate  from Vienna.  "The  nerve  of  her— coming  here  with  your  face!"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.98,0:12:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is not your lucky day.{she adds mo here, meaning the previous line was addressed to another girl who is not present}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.97,0:12:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I ever do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.82,0:12:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Might slap her on the face. \NLike you usually do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.91,0:12:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Would rather bite off that little nose of her. \N Nobody would say you two are alike then! {was unsure, but book resolved it for me: "Scratch  it  for  her,"  suggested  Monica. "The  best  thing  is  to  bite  her  nose  off,"  advised  Christine. "Then  you've  got  rid  of  the  cause  of  the  trouble  in  one stroke!"  She  swung  her  legs  lightheartedly  as  she  spoke. } {/Kill two birds with one stone}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.92,0:12:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My long-awaited summer vacation turned into this. \NWhat a bummer.{/.. ruined, it's the worst yet}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.92,0:12:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not like you can blame her for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.37,0:12:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Stephie?{just a very general "why"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.70,0:12:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just imagine it for a second: \Nsomebody else comes, looking exactly like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.86,0:12:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No way I can imagine that!{/unthinkable}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.25,0:12:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Who else in the world would be such a dope \Nas to go around looking like you!{damn, book is a life saver}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.81,0:12:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hear me out seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.45,0:12:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Luise, had you been in Lotte's shoes now,{/let's say if you've been lotte yourself}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.06,0:13:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, as Lotte, if you would have earned Luise's anger, \Nhow would you feel?{I hate how complicated this is, but then the next line is about how this all is hard to digest so I cope}{/and louise would take offence at you as lotte, what do you think?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.51,0:13:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I think...{/but...}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.49,0:13:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie! Say anything more convoluted \Nand we'll have our brains boil!{/please don't say something this こんがらがる anymore}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.17,0:13:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.89,0:13:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had been in Lotte's shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is so unbearable! \NYou just killed everyone's mood, Stephie!{I have no clue what is kurakunatchatte, kuroi is dark so maybe it's "made the atmosphere gloom" but I cant exclude "addled everyone's mind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't you think once before you speak?{/it's because you talk too much}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.79,0:13:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But hey...{/because/after all}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I know how to handle this.{/leave this to me} \NLet's go, Truda.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.78,0:13:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.72,0:13:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.01,0:14:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we really alike?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.90,0:14:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Christine. \NWe need to talk something over.{/need to have a talk with you}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Truda. \NIn Vienna, I go to the same class as Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.86,0:14:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Luise sure are alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.40,0:14:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's becoming a nuisance.{/troublesome}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.94,0:14:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A nuisance?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Like if I ever wanna talk to Luise, \Nbut end up babbling with you.{/say, I think I'm talking to louise but its actually you}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.45,0:14:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, I can't be bothered to ascertain \Nwho is who every single time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.89,0:14:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.81,0:14:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, don't come near Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.41,0:14:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We came here before you did, \Nso you should show some respect.{enryo is eserve; constraint; restraint; modesty; diffidence; hesitation; holding back; discretion; tact; thoughtfulness​\NNoun, Suru verb\N2. declining; refraining​\NNoun, Suru verb\N3. forethought; foresight​o and I genuinely dunno which one is implied}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.94,0:14:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.09,0:14:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.44,0:14:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Nina. We don't go to the same school, \Nyet Lotte and I became friends while we were on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.33,0:14:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you accuse Lotte of?{/what did lotte do, youre saying}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.18,0:14:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Should she even bear a striking semblance to some other girl, \Nhow can Lotte be held responsible for that?{more exact is rather "even if she troubles you with her similar face, isn't that the same (/equally troublesome) for lotte?" but I think it's too convoluted}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.00,0:14:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,'Bout that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.26,0:14:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't believe you can blow even such trifle \Nout of its proportion!{/make a problem out of such a thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.24,0:14:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.85,0:14:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that demeanor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.40,0:15:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All Munich girls have their noses in the air!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.25,0:15:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Lovely!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A better day comes tomorrow.{/will certainly be a good day}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.57,0:15:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Supper time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.34,0:15:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, from today on, \Nwe share a meal with our new friends from Munich.{/eating together with ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.30,0:15:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Make friends with them sooner, \Nto have loads of fun together!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.53,0:15:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a better look at Luise and Lotte \Nwhen they are sitting in one row.{unsure what she means, narabete means to line up/to arrange in a line}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.19,0:15:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean next to each other?\NWon't they start quarreling?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.74,0:15:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Times like this always call for decisive measures.{unsure why she words it like that: chiryoho is method of treatment; cure; remedy; also maybe she means not "such times as now" but "in that case/then"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.24,0:15:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.12,0:16:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Truda, won't you be so kind \Nas to free up this seat for Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.59,0:16:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.50,0:16:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Take that as my humble request.{/You shouldn't talk back/retort [to elders]}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.13,0:16:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.80,0:16:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll Luise do about it?\NOughta be a sight to behold!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.35,0:16:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone's getting slapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.51,0:16:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There she comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.94,0:16:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No difference at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.94,0:16:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't they sisters{guess}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.94,0:16:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, your seat would be right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.79,0:16:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a sinister silence. \NWhat's the matter, girls? Done eating already?{no clue whats owaranami, maybe owaru - to end/finish}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.42,0:16:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! She's about to cry!{/she did it, certain to break into tears}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.37,0:17:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How come this timid thing \Ndidn't break into tears?{/why didn't this girl start crying}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.70,0:17:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Things go far from smooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.30,0:17:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine, a person who is the spitting image of you \Nsuddenly barges in, what'll you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.87,0:17:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Probably, pinch myself to see if I'm awake.{/be perplexed/bewildered}\NThen, I'll try talking to this person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.34,0:17:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But why would you ask something like that?{/what does it have to do with our situation}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.46,0:17:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that obvious? \NSuch would be an adult's approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But those girls are just ten years old! Would take \Nthem some time to become comfortable with each other.{to open one's heart; to throw off reserve; to be frank}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.72,0:17:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two will figure it out.{/be alright} Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.36,0:17:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, we're also giving Lotte \Na bed next to Luise's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.26,0:17:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The sooner they grow closer - the better.{/grow intimate}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.29,0:18:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This over there is my bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.33,0:18:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But the counselor{really struggling but I can't come up with a better word} said I'm sleeping next to Luise.{/to go to the bed ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.90,0:18:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You've delivered Luise enough trouble today \Nby hanging around her!{/if you're next to louise, it's a nuisance to her}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.95,0:18:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You again! \NWhy are you being so rude to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.01,0:18:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you being so nosy?{/it's none of your business} \NShould keep your trap shut, Bavarian kid!{I have no clue what's ikoburi, koburi is A little small compared to others of the same kind. but what's that supposed to mean here? that she is a newcomer compared to them? she is younger?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.38,0:18:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My, can't believe all the girls in Vienna are so boorish!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.42,0:18:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told Vienna is a fantastic place,\Nand a Capital of Arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.58,0:18:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems, people inhabiting it \Nare still fresh out of cave!{/don't seem any big deal at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.56,0:18:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you mean by that? \NWe won't let you badmouth Vienna like that!{/won't forgive}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.67,0:18:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need your permission!{/I don't want your forgiveness}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.02,0:18:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Asking for a beating?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.12,0:18:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and try!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.36,0:18:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Stop it! I don't want you starting a brawl over me!{no clue what is keredo in the middle, dekiru? kenka? actually, kenka seems quite plausible - don't start a fight over me}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.11,0:18:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But why? Why are you so mad with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.17,0:19:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Counselor's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.50,0:19:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd you feel if you were in Lotte's shoes yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.17,0:19:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did I let it get on my nerves so much? \NI don't quite understand it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.55,0:19:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If dad had been here now, \Nwhat would he have to say?{/if I talked to dad about it}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.11,0:19:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, your spring and your candor{/liveliness and honesty} \Nare two things I appreciate the most about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.10,0:19:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,However, when you're about to speak your mind, \Ntake a moment to consider the feelings of others, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Mama...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.54,0:20:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, make sure to enjoy your vacations thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.35,0:20:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to make lots of friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.82,0:20:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You tend to be acting way too serious for your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.88,0:20:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not your fault, but mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.54,0:20:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Cooking, cleaning, washing{added} - \NI have to entrust everything to my little housekeeper!{unsure why she used minna here, it's usually for entities, not items}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.75,0:20:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Use this time for games, \Nlike the most ordinary child!{/to your hearts content with usual children}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.39,0:20:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,See that you come back \Nwith a lot of smile-wrinkles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.98,0:20:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, those wrinkles are not from smiling.{/it seems I can't produce dimples}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.66,0:21:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.90,0:21:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.92,0:21:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, I still can't be sure if I have the guts for it, \Nbut tomorrow, I'll try to talk things out with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.49,0:21:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,With the warmth of their hearts, \Nthe two girls started building the bond between them.{/in the space between ... something warm started flowing}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.06,0:21:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Like two magnets that first repel each other \Nwhen their identical poles meet, Luise and Lotte -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.65,0:21:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it{ between them} that draws them together despite everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Where this gentle moonlight shows the way, {/just like this ...}\Nlet's keep a close eye on those two.{unsure, maybe he means "the two will start watching over one another"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.29,0:21:53.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,To be continued
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.37,0:21:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.89,0:21:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.85,0:22:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte, do you usually let your mom brush your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.94,0:22:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been this way since I was little. Always.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.01,0:22:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.64,0:22:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But these days, I do it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.49,0:22:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no dad in our family, \Nso mom is constantly busy with work!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.27,0:22:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In our family, there's no mom. And our housekeeper Resi{rosa in english version but that would be blatantly off} \Njust can't stand it when she has to brush my hair.{lit is "is seems, ... doesn't like to brush children's hair" but that sounds kinda sus}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.81,0:22:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time - I and Myself: Thread of Fate{運命の糸}. \N{\i1}Look forward to it!{\i0}
